FreetuxTV is a Linux media player based on GTK+ and LibVLC for watching
and recording free WebTV, WebRadio and WebCam channels on a PC.

It can also be used for importing, watching and recording TV channels
from Tvheadend streaming server.

Features

- Add new groups of channels from M3U playlists
- Import and play TV and Radio channels from Tvheadend
- Listen WebRadio services
- Play TV (Free, SFR and WebTV)
- Play in fullscreen mode
- Play in mini mode
- Record selected channel
- Support for keyboard multimedia keys
- Timer recording
